Great food and nice chill atmosphere!

Solid service, fairly priced quality drinks, comfortable seating, right off the el with a view of the train. What more can you ask for? The food is great, but in my opinion quite pricey. For $7, you get only a handful of french fries.
Drinks are always made well! 👏🏻
Beautiful lounge in an interesting spot. Great food, too.

We frequent the Blue Line for the peanut butter and jelly martinis and I also love the tuna burger. Always a good atmosphere and the prices aren't bad for the area. The Blue Line is our go-to for a good happy hour.
Great food and fun, seasonal beverage options.
Very cozy for the holidays!
If you like 14 dollar cold cut sandwiches this is the spot for you
Great atmosphere and delicious food. Highly recommend the sriracha chicken sliders and fried mac and cheese bites 👌🏻

I take my family to this great restaurant from time to time! This is my favorite place to eat.  I visit this place frequently. The meals are great, the staff members are courteous and the prices are decent. I like eating in this restaurant for a tasty lunch.
Stopped in here for a quick cocktail before a show over at Subterranean - strong drinks, quick service, and great atmosphere. Will be back next time I'm in the area for a show!
Food was good and service was attentive. Nice relaxed vibe and cool atmosphere. Old movies playing was a nice touch.
Go grab a drink!
Great food, service and atmosphere.!! I will definitely be back.
Drinks are amazing... food not so much

Really great value during happy hour $6 martinis, yes please. Service is prompt and helpful if you're feeling indecisive. Plenty of martini options, something even for those who don't normally order one.  Bathrooms are clean. Patrons are chill.  Will be back.
Awesome place!! the staff is the best asset of this business!
Great Music tonight! Very fast service. Tatertots were perfectly crispy and soft insides. I had Lobster Mac and friend had Meaty Mac. Both dishes were awesome and filling.

Updating an old review, and giving that last star. Blue Line is that reliable neighborhood bar that everyone should have. Over the years they've made some changes to the food and drink menu, and updated the decor while keeping the charm. The food is great, particular favorites are the Drunken Chicken Panini, and the Chopped Salad. Drinks are always strong, and they have rotating specials on certain days of the week. Our favorite is Martini Wednesday, and they offer enough variety of "martini" to satisfy anyone's tastes.

Last week was the first time we came to that good restaurant. But It is surely not the last time. We passed a splendid evening with the attentive service, with the finest  dishes and wine and with the friendly payment. We will absolutely return there in a short time.

This was a place that I'd been wanting to try for a long time, but never got the chance to because I primarily drive in Chicago. However, we went here for a stop on my buddy's 21st birthday "bar tour" and this place had a GREAT Manhattan!! Their sliders are also very good. The prices for being in the heart of Wicker Park are impressively low. I also like how "ugly cute" it is inside.
Lobster roll rocked!  Glad we grabbed grub here!

Well... I'm always looking for a spot to go after work. Was on my way one place but ended up here instead. Food was very mediocre(wings & onion rings), I guess this is a place you go to drink. Cheapest 🍺 was five bucks.
In this neighborhood the place is a  good value.  A Library of board games for your pleasure.  Booths and high-tops available.  Food is good. The drinks we had were a value. Good atmosphere.
Fun place to go with friends.
I honestly love their food and service, fantastic area next to my home. The cashiers are always very nice. Highly recommended.
Awesome reasonable priced martini's, and an excellent attentive staff. Definitely a cool place to start the night.

I was visiting home because now I live in California but I was back in my area and found this spot underneath the blue line! You have to check this place out for the awesome drinks which they have a variety of and the food as well! Next time I am in town I will definitely be stopping by this spot as should you!!!!!
Excellent food and service
Decent 20s look
Airplane chicken rocks!
Food is good. Only bad thing was we waited forever to get our food when there wasn’t much people there.

One of our favorites in the neighborhood. Tasty martinis on special several happy hours each week (we like the Conductor, the lemon drop, and the Metrosexual); a good menu with above-average bar food options; lotta table spaces and bar stools; games; TV's showing old rat pack movies or Cary Grant-style black and whites and the home team games; attractive vintage decor; and friendly service.
Martini Wednesdays is a must! Bellini Martini 😋😋😋
Pbj martini is the BEST. Amazing food and service!
Great food and atmosphere !!!
Nice people all the time
Get the dirty martini.
Best martini in Chicago.
Only been for drinks. Solid martini and pbj martini is def worth a try. Weds has martini specials
Nice chill spot but check your glass of water to make sure nothing is floating around like what happened to me and make sure your utensils are clean. Mine and my girlfriend wasn't.

Jolly Rancher martini with sugar rim is hands down the best martini there! Sweet like candy (will not work for those with a bitter palate) and will definitely creep up on you later. Had the guac, hummus and pico de gallo platter which was okay, the pico de gallo had some after taste to it that was not good, then had the chicken spring rolls and those were amazing.
Reupholstered & redecorated. Same classic martinis and board games.
Solid, chill bar with a good food menu and some tasty cocktails. Staff are always super helpful!

Worst service of my life. After racking up a $100+ bill, and proceeding to order more drinks, the waitress,a white woman, approaches our table and asks "Was there a problem, because you didn't tip on the receipt."  I'm beyond offended. We paid for our order and ordered more ,but, before I could tip, in cash, the waitress comes to our table with this IGNORANT DISRESPECTFUL approach. After my facial expressions show my irritation and frustration, I ask for the manager. The manager , a white man, proceeds to tell me this isn't the first time he experienced this problem with his employee, but if it were to happen again, she would be terminated. The drinks we ordered came 20 minutes later, and the waitress said the drinks were on the house, but I told her I refused to have them comped, I wanted to pay for the drinks and I did. The disrespect I experienced was unbelievable. I will never go to this establishment again.
A bit over priced for the food. But drinks were cheap. Went on Wednesday night.
Does Allison still work the bar? She is the best bartender in Chicago, hands down! She always remember our group always offers a jello Shot in her. It’s little, but it just makes the difference.

Waited an hour on a slow Tuesday evening for mediocre wings and corn fritters that weren't actually corn fritters. To make matters worse, the aging doorman stared at my wife and I nearly the entire time we were there, which was awkward to say the least. We were the only Black people in the establishment, so maybe that's why? Too awkward and average to return. Thanks anyway.

Food was slightly overpriced for what was served.  Doesn't seem like the restaurant can decide on a theme, played music from 50s to 90s.  The mozzerella stuffed corn fritters aren't really corn fritters, they're more cheese balls.  Good selection of alcohol and beer.
Great drink specials! Great service. Very nice atmosphere. And super tasty martinis! Good food too. I love this place and would definitely recommend.
Cool spot
Chill, cozy, dope deco, good prices, definitely should check it out.
Blue Line Lounge is an underrated neighborhood classic! The wait staff are all angels, I love the martinis. I only wish it would open for brunch on weekends again!!!
Hip and cool, easy to relax with friends over drinks and food. Steps away from bustling 6 corners.
Best martinis
Good cocktails, fair prices, good vibe
One of my favorite chill places to get a drink when I'm in Chicago
One of my fav late night spots. Great martinis and specialty cocktails.
Great place for a cocktail especially on the days where they have $6 mojitos or martinis. Very good food as well!
Cool spot, good prices!
Great martinis and wonderful service
No specials what's so ever I got charged full price for 3 samples of beer. That's bad for business
Great service! Went here for chill NYE!

Val was an amazing server. I will definitely be going back again. It was my first time there and she was awesome.
Great Martinis and Food
Nice, casual atmosphere. Always enjoy stopping by after work.

Looks phenomenal after the renovations. It has an old school lounge look to it and is decently priced on food and drinks. Food is nothing special, but they have a variety of options with a good cocktail selection. It is never too crowded but has just enough to provide good atmosphere. It is a nice change if pace from the rest of the Wicker Park bars. I didn't give it 5 stars because it doesn't do anything outstanding itself except not be crowded and have a nice interior with decently friendly staff. I wouldn't go out of my way for this place but if you're in Wicker and looking for a slower pace bar then this is your spot.
Had fun here celebrating the holidays.
A neighborhood gem. Their cocktails are good and affordable for the neighborhood. The christmas decor was fantastic too!
Cozy place with great Christmas decor!✨🎁Sangria there was pretty good!
Awesome tunes and great happy hour
Love this place. Gets really loud at times. So not the place for intimate dates. Good is always good.
Love the atmosphere and martinis
I don't know why I like this place, but I do!
Me and my family enjoyed the food and wonderful music selection. Will be returning
Cool

I always walk by whenever I go to Big Star across the street, and one day I finally decided to stop in and have a meal. I loved it! I went on a Thursday night which was perfect because they weren't too busy and the staff were able to accommodate well. I love their decor especially with what they've done for the holidays (2018)! Overall I like the lounge vibe that they have compared to others that I've been to. It's not too busy and you can actually relax and focus on your drink and small bubble without the crowd being overwhelming. Thanks!
I never hanse any complaints when I come. Service is great. And they have some menu choices.
I went for the first time and the bartenders were so cool and friendly. They definitely gained my loyalty. I will keep coming back to say hi.
Had the most lovely bartender. Definitely coming back!
A very relaxed and chill spot. Centrally located by all of my favorite spots and to the El.

Good place for a beverage! We had just eaten so definitely weren't hungry so couldn't eat! Staff were friendly and there was a good vibe in the place! Would love to visit again and try the food if we are ever in Chicago again
Million dollar spaghetti was awesome!

Lovely atmosphere and love the train car style. Wait staff was very attentive and the food was phenomenal.  Drinks were strong and 2 were enough for me. I had the meatloaf which was awesome and the boyfriend had the pot pie which was huge! Definately will be back!
Exactly what I wanted in a lounge & grill - it was cozy, yummy and had great beer options!

It's worth going for their martini selections on Wednesdays when they're at the criminal price of $6!!! I loved their PB&J, Espresso, and Key Lime Pie ones along with some of the other eclectic choices. The fish tacos I had weren't that bad either. Of course, it's a convenient location for those who take the blue line.

Great Atmosphere!!!! I sat at the bar. I ordered a Jolly Rancher! Oh My!!! It was delicious! As a meal, I ordered a cheese burger with tator tots!!! My food came out delicious and piping hot! My only concern is the fact that there is a somewhat nice sized restroom that architecturally could hold 2 stalls. Instead, there's just 1. When I left out, there was a line. All and all, great place in the community. Plus, great location (right off the Damen CTA station).
Come every time we're in Chicago.

Bars like this are common in Chicago and Wicker Park in particular. Obviously it is convenient to the blue line. There are average price beers and cocktails that are all good. The food we got was an array of dips with a few toasted pita strips and tortilla chips. Not amazing, but not bad by any means. Chef Gordon Ramzi would probably rip them a new one for serving a dish that is obviously prepackaged spinach dip, hummus, and possibly prepackaged salsa. Meh, it tasted good with said chips except there was a lot more dip than there was stuff to put it on.

This place seemed alright until they did last call around 1:10am but my group figured we had a little bit of time to finish our drinks until staff abrasively yelled at us to leave at 1:20am also one of the bus boys was cursing at us to himself in Spanish. Only two stars because our waitress was awesome and a total sweetheart and for the 1 dollar Jell-O shots.
Great retro bar with excellent service.
Prompt service!
Passion fruit margarita was Awesome!
Great variety of food, friendly staff, and big TV's. Great seating and variety on drinks! Definitely coming back!
Excellent service and atmosphere

Went in for dinner and it was a great! We were seated immediately. We went in around 6pm on a Thursday. I had a salad that was wayyyyyy to spicy, I believe it was the buffalo chicken salad. I thought it would only be mildly spicy because that’s what I think when I hear buffalo chicken but nevertheless it was super spicy! And that’s speaking a lot since I am Mexican. I ordered a raspberry mojito which was really good. Our waitress was really attentive and nice. The only downside is sitting outside and having the train pass above you like ten trillion times. Other than that it was a great evening.
Awesome food and cocktails. Have daily specials like $6 martinis on Wednesday and Thursday Mojitos. Go and see Jordan the servers she is awesome.
I really like the vibe and my sangria was good
I love the bucktown salad! Its a nice place to stop and get a bite to eat. They had the booths redone too.
The bartender was attentive and knowledgeable regarding drinks offered at the bar. I was also presented with a food menu.
Service & Atmosphere was Great! Had the Chicken wrap & it had a good kick to it! Will definitely come back.
Great for a martini and awesome staff. Pub food is hit or miss, but a great spot overall.

amazing drinks, beautiful atmosphere.
Really good drinks here. Gotta go play the board games.

Love the newly remodeled lounge! The food is still fantastic, the service is well above standard, and I hate that I don't come here more often. An absolute must visit Chicago destination!
Great atmosphere and staff, never had a bad visit here. The upgrade did a great job cleaning it up without losing anything.

Great place, good food.....very loud

Went on $6 martini Wednesday with some friends....and er my gerd....loved every drink I drank. Didn't really eat much but sure had a glorious time. Will be returning.
Between the cocaine lady and the lemon drop, what more could you want?
The Cocktails are Really good. Liked the atmosphere! Nice sitting Booths.
Very nice Lounge good drinks and food pleasant staff.
Service was a little slow overall very nice place to have a few cocktails and people watch.
Went to this lounge for martini night and had an amazing time. The bar tender was very attentive and nice, and the martinis were made so well. Will return again
Been here since I don't know when,  at least 5 years.  Always great service. Good and martinis,  specially on wednesdays for their specials on them.  Keep up the good work guys!
Great list of cocktails and beers as well as awesome cocktail specials almost every day. The food is fantastic as well! Try the flatbreads and the fried Mac and cheese appetizer.

The drinks were good but the bartender didn’t know anything about the menu or the specialty shot. She asked someone else what the specialty shot was, we found out it was infused whisky but when i asked what it was infused with she just said Im not sure and walked away.
(Translated by Google) Great martoonis  (Original) Great martoonis
Love their Wednesday night martini deal, a great old time vibe in a hip neighborhood. Small plates great for sharing along with full entrees.

Conveniently next to it's eponymous train line. Decent snacks are available later into the evening. Beverages are reasonably priced for the area. With street level windows to the bustling crotch intersection of North Damen and Milwaukee, there's always something to entertain, even if your date is boring. Accepts credit cards.

Just went in for quick bite. The atmosphere was so comfortable!! The area in the back with the fireplace and nice couches was so cute and intimate!! It really feels like two places in one. VERY nice!! Just had drinks and wings, which was very good!! I loved the flavor of the wings but they weren't consistent, some were of average size while some were very small if it wasn't for this I would have given all of the stars
Food was just okay. Little overpriced for what you get
$6 All Martinis on Wednesday, $6 Mojito's Thursday! Awesome bar food!
Super chill

The comfiest seating and home of the $1 mystery jello shots! The mozzarella hush puppies are to die for, their selection of Moscow mules and specialty drinks won't disappoint (the key lime pie martini doesn't lie) and a trendy train cart themed atmosphere.
Great drinks, Uncrowded yet still active
Great local bar, with friendly atmosphere, and good food. Famous for it's Martinis.

Love this space one of my favorite places to grab a cocktail with friends. However the drinks used to taste a bit better & have a better presentation hence the 4 stars. The booths really need to be redone with all the rips as well.
$5 Martini wednesdays, the spot to be
what a great little find. great food and friendly staff.  great atmosphere

Place looked great before the remodel, looks even better now! Staff is phenomenal, friendly, quick. Great drink specials. Have only had a few food items, but everything has been solid bar food. Lots of TVs for sports and super convenient location. Love this place!
Martinis are affordable and delicious
The place had a nice vibe to it... our server was a bit in la la land but the bartender was Great!.. and the cocktails?... delicious
Drinks were on point

Fantastic cocktails, great food for snacking and sharing, and a fantastic environment makes the Blue Line Lounge and Grill a wonderful place to stop in for a few drinks. The crowd tapers off as the night goes on, so come early if you want to hang with other patrons or come late if you want a quiet end to your night. Located directly underneath the Blue Line!
Great good and decor.  Quick service and excellent drinks.
The renovations are great and the martinis are fabulous! It's a great girls night out!

The restaurant looked amazing. The French dip was ok, but the tater tots where awesome!

This is rather a well kept secret, even though its in a pretty public spot. I went there to try the brunch. Unfortunately, I had a slight hangover so the music and the guy yelling at the football on the screen didnt go over well with me.  This place is a bar. I dont know why they do a brunch, but hey, its wicker park. They just being they hipster selves. Brunch is what I went for, they lured me in with their 3$ mimosa and bloody mary advert.  I had the eggs and sausage which were pretty good, nothing spectacular. The mimosa was the shining star, and I will definitely be going back for that, as well as the stuffed waffle.  Oh and dont have the grits. They were like a weird tasteless porridge. The blonde waitress was pretty good and helpful, but the grits were recommended by the brunette who was international. Not listening to her again.
Beautiful atmosphere, happy hour on Thursdays, drink specials..
Convenient location must off the el.  Great burgers too.
Always good for a few martinis and a bite
Great place to go with a local crowd. No lines to get in and free of the typical late night drunks
A jewel
A good spot for happy hour drinks and good food.

One of my favorite places in the city. Its an old, dirty bar with a great location, and some of the best service in town. Stop by next time you are going to O'hare & have a few minutes to spare. (get the tacos & a martini)

Love the BL. A friendly neighborhood bar, themed on a  luxury train carraige, and right next to the Daman Blue Line CTA station.  Staff are friendly as are the patrons. No tap beer, only bottles. This place is famous for it's martinis. Wednesday nights gets busy due to its long running martini special night with $6 martinis.  Food is a combination of standard bar food and a few other items and occasional specials. The bar food is great, as are things like the pot pie, but avoid anything that sounds fancy or unusual.  One of the best bars in Wicker Park.
Great meeting place. Board games, some small TVS, and a really cute party room.
Lobster mac'n'cheese 😋
I don't usually get a chance to really explore the menu, but the burgers are good and the late night flatbread. Service is always on point. Don't miss martini Wednesday!
Great staff and drinks
I didn't  eat here,but the atmosphere  was very  nice.
Good place to go when everything else in the area has a line. Destination in and of itself in the winter.
Amazing cocktail menu, low prices...good crowd
The Mac and cheese skillets are so damn good, as well as their drinks. Definitely will return and recommend!

Always have well made cocktails and appetizers.  They have a nice martini selection that I like to explore. The spinach artichoke dip is a go to of mine, and their mini burgers and sweet potato fries are on point.
Great martini specials! Tasty food, fun games and good service. I love this bar!
Decent diner bar right off the blue line.
Delightful service and drinks.
They don't have crafted beer and some times the place smells kinda weird, but the grill oysters are delicious
This bar IS Chicago. Come start out here or end up here. Either way it's a win!! Music is on point and the drinks are superb.
Delicious!
Nice bar, not toi expensive
Atmosphere was good, staff was friendly, and the food was delicious.
Was there looking for a lost phone from the night before. Couldn't have been a more helpful staff at 10sm.
Nice for a Saturday afternoon and friendly staff.

I like Blue Line as a place where it's not too hard to get a table, the food is pretty decent, and the drinks are just fine as well. I wouldn't say there are any particular things that stand out here for me, but if you want to grab a decent and quick dinner around six corners before going out around that area, this is a solid choice.

Let me start by saying  that I like this place for drinks; however, the past 2 experiences have resulted in awful service. 45min wait from order placed  to served in a 50% full restaurant, unapologetic, and accusatory in tone. This is the same server that I had on another occasion that provided poor service. 3 of the people I was with said that they'll never return. If this was a onetime experience, I'd let it slide. Unfortunately, I think the only solution would be to retrain or fire this server to prevent this from occurring to other customers. If I'm contacted by management, I'd be happy to identify the server.

This atmosphere here completely saved our night, and was The highlight of our trip to Chicago!!!! We met the Owner, who is from the neighborhood. The Owner passionately operates his business with a love for his neighborhood. There are classic board games, and This Chicago gem is literally located just steps outside The entance to The blue line at Damen Station, The bartenders/servers  are friendly, inviting, and treated us like old friends. The drinks were perfect, and the food smelled amazing (wish I hadn't eaten before I got there) ... And the prices were reasonable! ....  Don't miss this place ... Worth it
Good brunch specials with cheap Bloody Marys.
Good specials, can usually grab a seat at the bar. Pretty decent snacks if you're hungry.
Awesome martinis!
Fantastic martinis!
a super cute and comfortable place to go for a drink. the staff is super helpful and kind. definitely going back!
Very much a diner feel but with a unique vibe. Service is always very good with a traditional American menu.
The ambiance was awesome and the drinks were amazing!
The blackened chicken sandwich was outstanding. Very inexpensive and good food. Our waitress was also extremely sweet and attentive. Would love to come again.

Came in on a thursday for their mojito special. It says on their website it's $4 but it's actually $5, they raised it somewhat recently. The space is great, good atmosphere and nice decor. We got a corner booth for our party of six. We all got different mojitos (they have a lot to choose from, the social is my favorite) They also have board games that you can play at the bar which is always an added bonus in my book. Had a great time grabbing drinks with friends and would definitely come back.
Cheap martinis!
Diner-style bar with good food options, open early on weekends.
French dip was mediocre and the atmosphere wasn't anything spectacular. Prices are about what you'd expect... ~ $15 a meal.
$5 Martinis every Wednesday night!
Great ambience and the wings and burgers were awesome. Board games kept my 12 year old off his phone for a nice touch.
Brunch was great here! Not crowded and service was pretty good

The place takes you back a few decades with the music from Frank Sinatra. The décor also was made around the same time since some of the upholstery is tearing apart. The service was great and fast. The skillets were OK and coffee as well.

I"ve been here a few times, but never had the chance to eat a meal here until last night.  In the past I"ve come here for an easy happy hour pr convenient drink as this spot, as the name indicates, is right next to the Damen blue line stop.  I love the ambiance here.  Class, but still casual enought to come in work out clothes as I often do.  The happy hour specials are always very reasonable and delicious.  Last night we ended up here on our way to a friend's place.  We chose the bbq brisket sandwich and Metropolitan salad.  The salad was a lovely combination of texture and flavors  The brisket sandwich was a lovely flavor, but a bit too bold and squishy to go unaccompanied by a coleslaw or other flavir and texture enhancer.  The cocaine lady martini was nice, but make sure you're in the mood for very sweet when you order it.  I don't believe service reviews should be accounted for in the stars rating, but I'll mention it.  We sat at the bar.  The woman who served us wasn't unfrienly, but she wasn't friendly if that makes sense.  Every other time I've been these though, the service was good to great.  I'd go back again!
Daily drink specials that can be found on small tabs dot com.  Can't speak on the food because I only come here for drinks.
